Real-Time Ousia [TM]

"Ousia" is picked from Greek, 
intend to represent the essence of Real-Time Theory.
Developed following K-I-S-S principle.


Source tree architecture
------------------------
core:
	Ousia core routines.
docs:
	Complete documentation of Ousia.
driver:
	Different kinds of device drivers based on Ousia.
	They are all confiurable.
framework:
	Framework based on Ousia. Such as print session, shell, etc.
	They are confiurable, either.
include:
	Header files of main routines of Ousia.
platform:
	Chip and board specific code. Ousia porting code are placed here.
sample:
	Sample code instances.
script:
	Useful scripts used while Ousia developing.
support:
	Basic supporting stuffs for Ousia developing and building.


acknowledgments
---------------
Some parts of the project are originally based on libmaple.
Thanks to their excellent works!
